Strawberry Bread
  --John Kanell

Bread:
3/4 c sugar (150g)
1/2 c whole milk (120mL)
1/2 c vegetable oil (120 mL)
1 large egg
1 1/2 tsp vanilla extract
2 c + 2 tbsp ap flour (255g)
2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1 1/2 c diced fresh strawberries (230g)

Preheat the oven to 350F. Lightly spray a 9x5" loaf pan with baking spray. In a medium bowl, whisk together the sugar, milk, oil, egg, and vanilla. In another medium bowl, stir together 2 c of flour, baking powder, and salt. Add the flour mixture to the sugar mixture and stir until just combined. In a small bowl, combine strawberries and 2 tbsp flour, tossing to coat strawberries. Fold the strawberries into the batter. Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan. Bake for 55-60 min or until a wooden pick inserted into the center comes out clean. Let the bread cool in the pan for 10 min. Remove the bread from the pan and cool completely on a wire rack.

Glaze:
3 tbsp diced fresh strawberries
1 c powdered sugar (120g)
1 tsp whole milk

Place the strawberries in a small bowl and mash. Stir in the powdered sugar and milk. Spoon over the cooled bread. Let stand for 30 minutes or until the glaze sets before serving.

